1 imbursement paid to an emergency medical services provider shall be equal to the amount of federal
2 financial participation received by the authority for the provider’s cost for the emergency medical
3 services.
4 (b) The Medicaid supplemental reimbursement paid to a provider under this section may not
5 exceed the provider’s actual costs for the emergency medical services, determined in accordance
6 with standards established by the authority, less the amount of reimbursement that the provider is
7 eligible to receive from all public and private sources.
8 (4) An emergency medical services provider shall make readily available to the authority doc-
9 umentation, data and certifications, as prescribed by the authority, necessary to establish that the
10 emergency medical services expenditures qualify for federal financial participation and to calculate
11 the amount of Medicaid supplemental reimbursement that is due.
12 (5)(a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, the authority shall modify the
13 method for calculating or paying the Medicaid supplemental reimbursement if modification is nec-
14 essary to ensure that emergency medical services expenditures qualify for federal financial partic-
15 ipation.
16 (b) This section does not authorize the payment of Medicaid supplemental reimbursement to an
17 emergency medical services provider if the provider has not entered into a provider agreement with
18 the authority, or a contract with a coordinated care organization, to serve medical assistance re-
19 cipients.
20 (c) If the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services approves the implementation of this sec-
21 tion and later revokes its approval or expresses its intent to revoke or refuse to renew its approval,
22 the authority shall report the fact at the next convening of the interim or regular session commit-
23 tees of the Legislative Assembly related to health care.
24 (6) General Fund moneys may not be used to implement this section, except as necessary to
25 certify an expenditure as eligible for federal financial participation. As a condition of receiving
26 Medicaid supplemental reimbursement, an emergency medical services provider must enter into and
27 comply with an agreement with the authority to reimburse the authority for the costs of adminis-
28 tering this section.
29 SECTION 2. ORS 413.235 is amended to read:
30 413.235. (1) To the extent allowed by federal law, the Oregon Health Authority shall develop
31 and implement [an intergovernmental transfer program] a funding mechanism to provide for the
32 transfer of funds [from] between an emergency medical services provider [to] and the authority to
33 pay the costs of providing emergency medical services to members of a coordinated care organiza-
34 tion. The authority shall pay any federal financial participation received by the authority as a re-
35 sult of the transfer of funds to the coordinated care organization. The coordinated care organization
36 shall increase, [by the same amount] by an amount specified by the authority, the amount of re-
37 imbursement paid to the emergency medical services provider for the costs of the emergency medical
38 services.
39 (2) The increased reimbursement paid under subsection (1) of this section shall be at least
40 actuarially equivalent to the Medicaid supplemental reimbursement for the emergency medical ser-
41 vices paid under ORS 413.234.
42 (3) General Fund moneys may not be used to implement this section, except as necessary to
43 certify an expenditure as eligible for federal financial participation. As a condition of [partic-
44 ipation in the intergovernmental transfer program] receiving the increased reimbursement de-
45 scribed in subsection (1) of this section, an emergency medical services provider must [agree to pay
[2]

